      • searchConcept

        public uk.ac.ebi.ep.enzyme.model.Entity searchConcept(BioportalOntology ontology,
                                             String query,
                                             Class<? extends uk.ac.ebi.ep.enzyme.model.Entity> clazz,
                                             boolean complete)
                                               throws BioportalAdapterException
        Searches BioPortal for a concept in one ontology.
        Parameters:
        ontology - The ontology to be searched in BioPortal.
        query - The text to search (a name, concept ID without ontology prefix...).
        clazz - The type of the returned entity.
        complete - query BioPortal again with the concept ID in order to get additional info? If true, the entity is completed (see completeEntity(Entity, String, String), otherwise it will contain just ID, name and URL.
        Returns:
        an Entity object of the specified type and the level of detail matching exactly the query, or null if not found. Note that if the search returns more than one result, only the first one is considered (this fact will be logged, though).
        Throws:
        BioportalAdapterException

      • searchConcept

        public Set<uk.ac.ebi.ep.enzyme.model.Entity> searchConcept(BioportalOntology[] ontologies,
                                                  String query,
                                                  Class<? extends uk.ac.ebi.ep.enzyme.model.Entity> clazz,
                                                  boolean complete)
                                                    throws BioportalAdapterException
        Searches BioPortal for a concept in several ontologies.
        Parameters:
        ontologies - The ontologies to be searched in BioPortal.
        query - The text to search (a name, concept ID without ontology prefix...).
        clazz - The type of the returned entity.
        complete - query BioPortal again with the concept ID in order to get additional info? If true, the entity is completed (see completeEntity(Entity, String, String), otherwise it will contain just ID, name and URL.
        Returns:
        a collection of Entity objects of the specified type and the level of detail matching exactly the query, or null if none found.
        Throws:
        BioportalAdapterException
